urdb_response.description:
Applies to all electric service for domestic purposes in each individual metered residence, apartment unit,
mobile home, or other dwelling unit whose point of delivery is at secondary voltage less than 12,470 volts
nominal line to line located within the limits of Austin Energy's service territory. The rate tables below
reflect rates with effective dates of November 1, 2018.
urdb_response.name: Residential
urdb_response.energycomments: Adjustments = Power Supply Adjustment Charge + Regulatory Charge + Community Benefit Charges
